data.chText: （旧时南非的）黑人城镇，黑人居住区
data.enText: (in South Africa in the past) a town or part of a town that black people had to live in, and where only black people lived

data.chText: 镇区（美国和加拿大县以下一级的地方政府）
data.enText: (in the US or Canada) a division of a county that is a unit of local government

means: (旧时南非的)黑人城镇，黑人居住区
镇区(美国和加拿大县以下一级的地方政府)

tr: an administrative division of a county
example: the town is responsible for snow removal

value.def: In South Africa, a township was a town where only black people lived.
value.tran: (过去南非的)黑人城镇，黑人居住区

value.def: In the United States and Canada, a township is an area of land, especially a part of a county which is organized as a unit of local government.
value.tran: 区，镇区(美国及加拿大县的下一级行政区)

trans: 乡镇企业；农村居民和乡镇企业；中国的乡镇企业
